# .fernignore
#
# Files listed here are hand-maintained and MUST be preserved across SDK
# regeneration. They implement the Idempotency-Key auto-mint patch: when a
# caller does not set an Idempotency-Key header on one of the five POST send
# endpoints (/messages/send, /messages/{id}/reply, /reply-all, /forward,
# /drafts/{id}/send), the core request path mints a single UUID4 once and sets
# it as the Idempotency-Key header BEFORE the retry loop, so all internal
# retries carry the same key. Do not let codegen overwrite or delete these.

# New, non-generated files (the patch itself + its tests).
internal/requestconfig/idempotency.go
internal/requestconfig/idempotency_test.go

# Generated file with a hand-added call site: maybeSetIdempotencyKey(cfg.Request)
# is invoked in Execute() immediately before the retry loop. If regeneration
# overwrites this file, re-apply that single call.
internal/requestconfig/requestconfig.go
